{
  "analysis": "The previous probe produced noisy stderr and did not give clean evidence. We still do not have a working arithmetic encoder for non-empty streams; generated test files decode incorrectly and /app/decomp outputs nothing. The key remaining hypothesis is that the decoder normalizes before reading each bit, so the encoder must normalize before computing the bit interval, and it must maintain fraction exactly. We need test this exact state-driven encoder on tiny cases before attempting the full data compression.",
  "plan": "Rewrite genseq.c as an exact decoder-state-driven encoder: put_bit normalizes first, computes split, updates low/range/fraction/cc according to desired bit, then normalizes. put_integer mirrors the decoder exactly. Test 0 tokens, one literal 1, two literals 1 and 2, and match offset 1 length 1 using /app/decomp and decsim diagnostics. If small tests pass, we can proceed to data parsing; if not, the logs will reveal where divergence occurs.",
  "commands": [
